This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it specifically studies the structure and evolution of the Internet's Autonomous System (AS) interconnection topology. It also involves game theory, which suggests it could also belong to the sub-category of Game Theory and Decision Science (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper discusses static and dynamic aspects of the game, which could place it in the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Information Theory (cs.IT), respectively. Finally, the paper mentions utility transfers between players, which could also place it in the sub-category of Computational Economics (cs.CE).
